2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK%20Woman%20Almost%20Loses%20Vision%20After%20Contact%20Lenses%20Cause%20Ulcer%20On%20Her%20Eye%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%2025-year-old%20woman%20in%20the%20UK%20nearly%20lost%20her%20vision%20after%20she%20developed%20an%20ulcer%20on%20her%20eye%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-wales-66830112%5C%22%3EBBC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20According%20to%20the%20doctors%2C%20the%20ulcer%20was%20caused%20by%20her%20contact%20lenses.%20Notably%2C%C2%A0Steph%20Carrasco%20was%20suffering%20itchiness%20in%20her%20eye%2C%20following%20which%20she%20consulted%20an%20eye%20doctor.%20She%20simply%20thought%20she%20was%20having%20some%20irritation%20from%20daily%20contact%20use.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20her%20problem%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20much%20more%20serious%20as%20the%20eye%20doctor%20told%20her%20she%20had%20''aggressive%20bacteria''%20in%20her%20eye%2C%20which%20had%20caused%20the%20ulcer%20on%20the%20cornea.%20Her%20optometrist%20then%20referred%20her%20to%20a%20specialist%20eye%20hospital.%20She%20spent%20one%20week%20in%20the%20hospital%2C%C2%A0with%2072%20drops%20of%20antibiotics%20administered%20to%20her%20eye%20daily%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20reduce%20the%20ulcer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMs%20Carrasco%20said%2C%20''By%20the%20time%20I%20was%20admitted%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20I%20could%20barely%20see.%20It%20was%20terrifying.%C2%A0It%20was%20terrifying.%20Thankfully%2C%20Jack%20and%20the%20team%20were%20outstanding.%20He%20made%20sure%20I%20didn't%20leave%20the%20Specsavers%20store%20until%20he%20had%20arranged%20plans%20with%20the%20hospital%20and%20kept%20me%20reassured%20during%20an%20incredibly%20stressful%20time.%20He%20was%20quick%20thinking%20and%20thorough%20-%20I%20couldn't%20be%20more%20grateful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cul%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%20%3Cul%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20daily%20dose%20of%20antibiotics%2C%20the%20ulcer%20did%20not%20heal%2C%20leaving%20the%C2%A0medical%20staff%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20perform%20a%20cornea%20transplant.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThree%20weeks%20on%2C%20her%20vision%20has%20improved%2C%20and%20it%20is%20hoped%20it%20will%20return%20in%20full%20by%20October%2C%20allowing%20her%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work.%C2%A0She%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20told%20by%20the%20medical%20staff%20at%20the%20hospital%20that%20the%20bacteria%20in%20my%20eye%20was%20so%20harsh%20that%20if%20it%20had%20been%20left%20any%20longer%2C%20I%20would%20have%20lost%20my%20eye%20completely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Farticles%2F10737-contacts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECleveland%20Clinic%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20corneal%20ulcers%20are%20usually%20caused%20by%20an%20infection%20or%20severe%20dry%20eye%2C%20but%20those%20who%20wear%20contact%20lenses%20may%20be%20particularly%20at%20risk%20if%20they%20don't%20clean%20their%20lenses%20correctly%20or%20leave%20them%20in%20too%20long%2C%20While%C2%A0most%20ulcers%20can%20be%20treated%20with%20antibiotics%20or%20antifungal%20eye%20drops%2C%20severe%20cases%20can%20lead%20to%20permanent%20sight%20loss%20through%20scarring.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOptometrist%20Jack%20Brenton%2C%20who%20initially%20treated%20Ms%20Carrasco%20spoke%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20having%20a%20sight%20test%20every%20two%20years%20and%20consulting%20an%20optometrist%20immediately%20if%20people%20have%20any%20concerns%20about%20their%20eyes%20or%20vision.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFortunately%2C%20Steph%20is%20already%20on%20the%20road%20to%20recovery%20and%20we%20hope%20her%20vision%20will%20be%20back%20to%20normal%20within%20a%20month%2C%20but%20her%20story%20is%20a%20case-in-point%20of%20why%20a%20rapid%20medical%20assessment%20is%20so%20crucial%2C''%20he%20noted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%2