rom%20the%20state's%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20%E2%80%94%20who%20was%20first%20elected%20mayor%20in%202019%20and%20reelected%20earlier%20this%20year%20with%2098.7%25%20of%20the%20vote%20%E2%80%94%20took%20to%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Famericas-cities-need-republicans-and-im-becoming-one-dallas-texas-mayor-965dbaa4%5C%22%3Eannounce%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20party%20switch%2C%20where%20he%20criticized%20his%20old%20party%20while%20insisting%20that%20the%20GOP%20needed%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20the%20conversation%20in%20the%20country's%20biggest%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-type%3D%5C%22paragraph%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThe%20future%20of%20America's%20great%20urban%20centers%20depends%20on%20the%20willingness%20of%20the%20nation's%20mayors%20to%20champion%20law%20and%20order%20and%20practice%20fiscal%20conservatism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BOur%20cities%20desperately%20need%20the%20genuine%20commitment%20to%20these%20principles%20(as%20opposed%20to%20the%20inconsistent%2C%20poll-driven%20commitment%20of%20many%20Democrats)%20that%20has%20long%20been%20a%20defining%20characteristic%20of%20the%20GOP.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-type%3D%5C%22paragraph%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BIn%20other%20words%2C%20American%20cities%20need%20Republicans%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Republicans%20need%20American%20cities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20my%20political%20hero%20Theodore%20Roosevelt%20was%20born%2C%20only%2020%25%20of%20Americans%20lived%20in%20urban%20areas.%20By%20the%20time%20he%20was%20elected%20president%2C%20that%20share%20had%20doubled%20to%2040%25.%20Today%2C%20it%20stands%20at%2080%25.%20As%20America's%20cities%20go%2C%20so%20goes%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-type%3D%5C%22paragraph%5C%22%3EIn%20the%201990s%2C%20GOP%20figures%2C%20including%20Rudy%20Giuliani%20and%20Richard%20Riordan%2C%20won%20the%20mayoralties%20of%20New%20York%20and%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20respecti