20over%20a%20period%20of%2050%20years%20or%20so.%20The%20poems%20have%20been%20perfectly%20translated%20in%20English%20by%20N%20Venugopal%20and%20Meena%20Kandasamy.%20This%20happens%20to%20be%20the%20first%20translation%20ever%20of%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20poetry%20in%20English.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20278px)%2085vw%2C%20278px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24183157%2Fcontent-182x300.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22278%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24183157%2Fcontent-182x300.jpeg%20182w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24183157%2Fcontent-621x1024.jpeg%20621w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24183157%2Fcontent.jpeg%20728w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674606%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22458%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20Life%20in%20Poetry%20by%20Varavara%20Rao.%20Publisher%3A%20Penguin%20Random%20House%20India%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20essay%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENecessity%20of%20Atheism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Percy%20Shelly%20identifies%20three%20indicators%20for%20the%20non-existence%20of%20God%20%E2%80%93%20lack%20of%20sensory%20input%2C%20presence%20of%20reason%20and%20an%20absence%20of%20testimony%20of%20God%E2%80%99s%20presence.%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20poetry%20is%20similar%20to%20these%20three%20%E2%80%9Cexcitements%E2%80%9D%20as%20Shelly%20calls%20them%2C%20for%20rightly%20refuting%20the%20existence%20of%20order%20and%20equality%20in%20Indian%20society.%20The%2048%20poems%20trace%20the%20timeline%20of%20the%20historical%20inevitability%20that%20India%20is.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20book%20of%20modern%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20defining%20moments%20captured%20through%20absolutely%20stunning%20language%20and%20pain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20as%20we%20set%20on%20a%20path%20to%20decipher%20Rao%2C%20the%20poet%2C%20he%20reveals%20himself.%20His%20own%20analysis%20of%20poetry%20is%20like%20the%20spirit%20of%20a%20free%20bird%20and%20his%20language%20its%20wings.%20In%20a%20poem%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPoetry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Rao%20says%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPoetry%20is%20truth%20that%20need%20not%20be%20concealed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20who%20do%20not%20need%20government%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELife%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20need%20ambrosia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20keeping%20up%20his%20words%2C%20Rao%20has%20not%20hidden%20any%20truth%20which%20was%20worth%20the%20salt%20throughout%20his%20life%20as%20well%20as%20in%20this%20anthology%20of%20his%20poetry.%20The%20unwanted%20ambrosia%20of%20life%20is%20akin%20to%20Faiz%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esheereeni-e-farda%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20his%20famous%20poem%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDua%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Faiz%20had%20written%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAaiye%20arz%20guzarein%2C%20k%20nigaar-e-hasti%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EZeher-e-imroz%20mein%20sheereeni-e-farda%20bhar%20de%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(Come%20let%20us%20pray%20that%20the%20creator%20may%20fill%20sweetness%20in%20tomorrow%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Etaking%20away%20the%20poison%20of%20today).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sweet%20nectar%20of%20tomorrow%20is%20thus%20a%20promise%20of%20hope%20for%20both%20the%20hopeful%20Faiz%20as%20well%20as%20for%20the%20not%20so%20hopeful%20Rao%20but%20it%20is%20the%20%E2%80%98poison%20of%20today%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20fills%20the%20lives%20of%20common%20people%2C%20that%20finds%20its%20way%20in%20their%20recitations.%20Both%20are%20thus%20peoples%E2%80%99%20poets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20young%20teenager%20I%20still%20remember%20the%20day%20when%20in%20September%2C%201987%2C%20Roop%20Kanwar%2C%20a%20married%20Rajasthani%20girl%20was%20burnt%20on%20the%20pyre%20of%20her%20husband%20as%20part%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESati%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20tradition.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20haunting%20poems%20of%20this%20anthology%20is%20a%20poem%20describing%20Roop%E2%80%99s%20plight.%20It%E2%80%99s%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EChunri%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20is%20a%20revelation%20of%20this%20mediaeval%20tradition%20of%20gruesome%20patriarchy.%20The%20last%20verses%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EChunri%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20are%20heartbreaking%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20true%20that%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20dragged%20her%20on%20his%20pyre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20he%20would%20drag%20her%20on%20his%20bed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20same%20authority.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20performed%20Sati%20as%20freely%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20she%20lived%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQualifying%20something%20as%20brutal%20and%20ugly%20as%20misogyny%20through%20poetry%20is%20what%20makes%20Rao%20a%20poet%20worth%20reading.%20He%20holds%20our%20hand%20and%20walks%20us%20into%20a%20cold%20dark%20space%20where%20life%20is%20not%20what%20we%20are%20made%20to%20believe.%20There%20is%20rather%20an%20infinite%20absence%20of%20life%20all%20around%20in%20that%20real%20space.%20His%20poem%20reminds%20me%20of%20Sylvia%20Plath%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELady%20Lazarus%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%20it%2C%20she%20says%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20done%20it%20again.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20year%20in%20every%20ten%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20manage%20it%E2%80%94%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20sort%20of%20walking%20miracle%2C%20my%20skin%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBright%20as%20a%20Nazi%20lampshade%2C%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20right%20foot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20paperweight%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20face%20a%20featureless%2C%20fine%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJew%20linen%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20%E2%80%98Nazi%20lampshade%E2%80%99%20of%20Plath%E2%80%99s%2C%20to%20me%2C%20finds%20reflection%20in%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20Sati.%20Both%20have%20a%20poignant%20theatrical%20value%20in%20their%20verses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20book%2C%20Meena%20Kandasamy%20says%20that%20Rao%20is%20perhaps%20the%20longest%20jailed%20poet%20in%20independent%20India%E2%80%99s%20history.%20Like%20the%20Spanish%20poet%20Federico%20Garcia%20Lorca%2C%20imprisonment%20probably%20sets%20the%20poet%20free.%20Lorca%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Prisoner%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Etells%20us%20about%20that%20girl%20lost%20in%20the%20dark%20night%20who%20reflected%20daylight%20with%20the%20splendor%20of%20her%20unclouded%20forehead.%20Rao%20uses%20less%20metaphors%20and%20more%20realism%20when%20he%20writes%20about%20the%20prison.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fvaravara-rao-young-poet-public-statement%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Attack%20on%20Varavara%20Rao%20Is%20an%20Attack%20on%20All%20of%20Us%E2%80%99%3A%20Young%20Poets%20Urge%20Release%20of%20Activist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20poem%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESab%20Theekh%20Hai%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewritten%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eduring%20his%20second%20jail%20sentence%20between%20May%201974%20and%20April%201975%2C%20Rao%20describes%20how%20the%20tired%20night%20guards%20screamed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esab%20theekh%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(all%20is%20well)%20every%20hour.%20The%20metaphorical%20beauty%20of%20this%20poem%20is%20difficult%20to%20describe%20in%20words.%20Rao%20writes%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20moon%20gets%20caught%20in%20the%20barbed%20wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20the%20prison%20walls.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20we%2C%20after%20singing%20and%20talking%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELose%20ourselves%20in%20the%20dreams%20of%20revolution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20difficulty%20of%20these%20verses%20is%20not%20the%20presence%20of%20metaphors%20but%20the%20inability%20to%20distinguish%20between%20metaphors%20and%20corporeality.%20They%20are%20blended%20like%20the%20dusk%20and%20the%20night.%20The%20moon%2C%20the%20barbed%20wire%2C%20prison%20walls%2C%20singing%20or%20maybe%20the%20dream%20of%20revolution%20%E2%80%93%20all%20fall%20in%20the%20preview%20of%20our%20own%20perception%20and%20conscious%20volition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20can%20we%20infer%20in%20a%20society%20which%20harbours%20death%20and%20life%2C%20joy%20and%20sadness%2C%20poverty%20and%20richness%2C%20hunger%20and%20satiety%20with%20equal%20passive%20perception%3F%20What%20happens%20when%20nations%20make%20sad%20metaphors%20an%20actuality%3F%20Isn%E2%80%99t%20it%20ironic%20that%20such%20a%20poem%20is%20published%20in%20times%20when%20the%20highest%20executive%20of%20the%20nation%20made%20a%20similar%20comment%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESab%20changa%20si%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(all%20is%20well).%20Remember%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndeed%2C%20poets%20have%20a%20prophetic%20appeal!%20They%20know%20the%20future%20better%20than%20us.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFriedrich%20Nietzsche%20had%20once%20written%20that%20if%20you%20kill%20a%20cockroach%2C%20you%20are%20a%20hero%2C%20if%20you%20kill%20a%20butterfly%2C%20you%20are%20evil.%20Morals%20have%20aesthetic%20criteria.%20The%20aesthetics%20of%20morality%20is%20thus%20a%20slippery%20slope.%20The%20reality%20of%20this%20aesthetic%20criteria%20is%20best%20demonstrated%20by%20Rao%20in%20a%20poem%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ED%C3%A9j%C3%A0%20vu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20He%20writes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELucky%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20are%20born%20rich.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20you%20say%20in%20your%20lingo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Born%20with%20a%20silver%20spoon%20in%20the%20mouth%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYour%20agitation%20sounds%20creative%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20agony%20appears%20violent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20can%20deflate%20tyres%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20artistic%20elan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20indulgent%20police%20look%20on%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETheir%20jaws%20nestling%20on%20rifle%20butts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20are%20told%20that%20this%20poem%20was%20written%20by%20Rao%20following%20an%20agitation%20of%20the%20upper%20caste%2C%20upper%20class%20youths%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20in%201986%20against%20a%20state%20level%20commission%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20for%20increasing%20reservations.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20apt%20representation%20of%20what%20Nietzsche%20had%20inferred%20a%20few%20decades%20back.%20In%20%E2%80%98merit%20hungry%20nations%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20right%20to%20protest%20is%20only%20with%20those%20who%20hardly%20need%20protests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20we%20speak%20of%20poetry%2C%20we%20speak%20of%20chaos.%20Poetry%20which%20invokes%20chaos%20is%20poetry%20which%20gives%20hope.%20Hope%20lies%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20chaos.%20In%20a%20nation%20which%20is%20reeling%20under%20majoritarianism%2C%20communalism%20and%20casteism%2C%20what%20hope%20can%20we%20infer%20from%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20poetry%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20pretence%20of%20hope%20has%20been%20endured%20since%20eternity%20and%20poets%20are%20the%20harbingers%20of%20this%20pretence.%20Some%20like%20Rao%20have%20been%20bestowed%20the%20job%20of%20making%20the%20pretence%20real.%20They%20work%20to%20make%20us%20believe%20in%20hope.%20Despite%20incarceration%2C%20despite%20state%20suppression%20to%20curb%20his%20spirits%2C%20and%20despite%20all%20methods%20to%20drown%20his%20voice%2C%20Rao%20roars%20with%20his%20poetry%20like%20a%20waterfall.%20His%20infectious%20courage%20makes%20those%20in%20power%20nervous%20as%20armed%20with%20such%20poignant%20beautiful%20poetry%2C%20Rao%20is%20a%20force%20to%20reckon%20with.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Dream%20Pigeons%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20he%20writes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPigeons%20released%20by%20heart%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAlight%20on%20the%20eyelids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20know%20I%20am%20scared%20to%20open%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20eyes%20and%20break%20the%20wings%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20so%2C%20I%20pretend%2C%20with%20my%20eyes%20closed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20know%20very%20well%20that%20my%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDreams%20are%20not%20my%20creations%20alone%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20that%20imagination%20is%20not%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnyone%E2%80%99s%20secret.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMay%20his%20dream%20come%20true%20and%20may%20his%20imagination%20be%20on%20fire%2C%20always.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShah%20Alam%20Khan%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Orthopaedics%2C%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%2C%20New%20Delhi.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695563136000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F26100034%2FVaravara-Rao-flowers-collage.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwhen-the-moon-gets-caught-in-the-barbed-wire-over-the-prison-wall-varavara-rao-poetry%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Life%20in%20Poetry%20is%20an%20anthology%20of%2048%20poems%20written%20by%20Telugu%20poet-activist%20Varavara%20Rao%2C%20written%20over%20a%20period%20of%2050%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwhen-the-moon-gets-caught-in-the-barbed-wire-over-the-prison-wall-varavara-rao-poetry%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parineeti%20Chopra-Raghav%20Chadha%20Wedding%3A%20Why%20Karan%20Johar%20Didn't%20Attend%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A