207%20am%20on%20a%20Saturday%20when%20I%20meet%20up%20with%20CC.%20She%20is%20in%20wet%20boots%20and%20has%20her%20task%20list%20in%20hand.%20I%20sat%20in%20her%20car%20along%20with%20Lucy%2C%20her%20dog%20and%20two%20cats%2C%20Charles%20and%20Puss.%20Before%20feeding%20her%20horse%2C%20she%20gave%20me%20a%20mini%20tour%20of%20her%20thorny%20paradise.%20Most%20of%20her%20farm%20is%20not%20cultivable%20due%20to%20scarcity%20of%20water%2C%20sandy%20soil%20or%20hilly%20terrain.%20In%20other%20parts%2C%20she%20let%20junipers%2C%20cedars%2C%20cactuses%20and%20even%20the%20desert%20rat%20run%20wild.%C2%A0%20Swerving%20on%20the%20sand%20trail%2C%20we%20reach%20the%20horses.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFour%20hungry%20horses%20ran%20towards%20us%2C%20we%20quickly%20give%20them%20a%20corn%20and%20hay%20breakfast.%20Next%2C%20we%20have%20to%20activate%20the%20gravity%20fed%20water%20sprinklers.%20Here%20is%20where%20I%20notice%20adolescent%20wheat%20plants%20shining%20in%20the%20morning%20sun.%20They%20are%20unlike%20the%20%E2%80%9CGreen%20Revolution%E2%80%9D%20wheat%20varieties%2C%20so%20I%20ask%20about%20them.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20Spanish%20Sonora%20wheat.%20They%20bought%20this%20over%20in%20the%2015%20century.%20Over%20time%20newer%20varieties%20came%2C%20and%20this%20seed%20was%20lost.%20Today%20we%20have%20revived%20this%20variety%20and%20also%20started%20giving%20it%20to%20other%20farmers%20to%20grow%20and%20to%20community%20members%20and%20restaurants%20as%20flour.%20This%20seed%20is%20part%20of%20New%20Mexico%20heritage%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%20in%20the%20US%2C%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20craze%20for%20Sonora%20seeds%20and%20flour%20in%20the%20regenerative%20agriculture%20world.%20Before%20the%20Spanish%2C%20the%20Americas%20did%20not%20have%20wheat.%20So%20Sonora%20wheat%20plays%20an%20important%20historical-cultural%20role.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20farm%20and%20foundation%2C%20Owl%20Peak%2C%20is%20currently%20researching%20this%20hardy%20wheat%20for%20its%20cover%20crop%2C%20harvesting%20potential%20and%20its%20possibilities%20in%20building%20soil%20in%20the%20high%20desert.%20Conversation%20with%20bakers%20and%20restaurants%20in%20Santa%20Fe%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20Sonora%20wheat%20is%20growing%20to%20be%20the%20customer%E2%80%99s%20choice%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185046%2FIMG_0318.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185046%2FIMG_0318.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185046%2FIMG_0318-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185046%2FIMG_0318-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674612%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECulver%E2%80%99s%20farm%20in%20La%20Madera%2C%20New%20Mexico.%3Cbr%3EPhoto%3A%20Indra%20Shekhar%20Singh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENext%20it%20is%20time%20to%20feed%20the%20chickens%20and%20see%20the%20garlic%20fields.%20So%20we%20drive%20on%20the%20sandy%20trail%20towards%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Earroyo%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20then%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20chickens%20house.%20As%20we%20enter%20the%20farm%2C%20CC%20takes%20me%20down%20memory%20lane.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20the%20first%20farm%20I%20starting%20to%20work%20on%2C%20it%20was%20nothing%20like%20this%20when%20we%20started.%20The%20soil%20was%20very%20bad%2C%20the%20house%2C%20toolshed%20and%20green%20house%20weren%E2%80%99t%20there.%20We%20made%20all%20of%20it%2C%20and%20simultaneously%20started%20the%20experiments%20with%20soil%20building%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20different%20sections%20of%20the%20farm.%20From%20permaculture%20to%20Hugelkultur%20pits%2C%20she%20has%20tried%20to%20employ%20the%20best%20ideas%20to%20build%20soils%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%2C%20eco-agri%20researchers%20and%20experts%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world%20have%20come%20here%20and%20tried%20to%20tell%20us%20what%20to%20do.%20We%20even%20tried%20to%20implement%20their%20designs%20and%20techniques.%20Most%20of%20them%20simply%20failed%20because%20the%20desert%20is%20a%20hard%20place%20and%20it%20has%20its%20own%20way.%20Over%20time%20I%20came%20to%20understand%20and%20live%20with%20this.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20had%20extreme%20drought%20for%20many%20years%2C%20and%20then%20randomly%20we%20received%20an%20above%20average%20snowfall%2C%20or%20a%20regular%20monsoon%20season%2C%20giving%20us%20just%20enough%20to%20survive.%20I%20try%20to%20observe%2C%20adapt%2C%E2%80%9D%20CC%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20quickly%20disappears%20in%20the%20chicken%20coop%20and%20the%20little%20birds%20are%20upon%20her.%20A%20mixed%20corn%20meal%2C%20two%20packets%20of%20salad%20leaves%20and%20some%20fresh%20water%20is%20served.%20In%20return%20we%20collect%20some%20of%20multicoloured%20eggs%20and%20walked%20to%20the%20greenhouse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20the%20fig%20tree%20and%20Japanese%20mustard%20samplings%20we%20talked%20about%20her%20eco-agri%20pedagogue.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20is%20this%20is%20for%20the%20community.%20Overtime%20we%20have%20empowered%20many%20of%20the%20community%20members%20to%20join%20us%20here%20for%20residencies%20in%20eco-agriculture%2C%20food%2C%20environment%20and%20art.%20We%20had%20an%20indigenous%20chilly%20project%2C%20amaranth%20revival%20project%2C%20blue%20corn%20project%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%20but%20many%20artists%20and%20chefs%20have%20also%20worked%20on%20food%20here.%20Our%20farm%20has%20hosted%20%E2%80%98donation%20only%E2%80%99%20meals%2C%20to%20bring%20the%20community%20together.%20A%20platform%20where%20people%20can%20meet%20and%20grow%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%20while%20plucking%20some%20green%20herbs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20like%20to%20support%20people%2C%20be%20themselves%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20384px)%2085vw%2C%20384px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185139%2FIMG_0328-e1695561729943.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185139%2FIMG_0328-e1695561729943.jpeg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185139%2FIMG_0328-e1695561729943-225x300.jpeg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185139%2FIMG_0328-e1695561729943-768x1024.jpeg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674613%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECulver%E2%80%99s%20farm%20in%20La%20Madera%2C%20New%20Mexico.%3Cbr%3EPhoto%3A%20Indra%20Shekhar%20Singh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20ask%20about%20blue%20corn%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20getting%20to%20that.%E2%80%9D%20Off%20we%20went%20to%20Dora%E2%80%99s%20Farm.%20There%20is%20no%20Dora%20in%20the%20picture%20anymore%2C%20but%20CC%E2%80%99s%20third%20farm%20is%20named%20after%20its%20original%20owner.%20She%20and%20her%20team%20manage%2012%20acres%20%E2%80%93%20a%20size%20which%20is%20considered%20a%20very%20small%20farm%20in%20America.%20At%20Dora%E2%80%99s%20Farm%2C%20she%20introduces%20me%20to%20a%20Mexican%20man%2C%20Roberto%2C%20the%20farm%20manager.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20worked%20together%20as%20a%20team%20for%20many%20years%20now%2C%20trying%20to%20rejuvenate%20the%20place.%20I%20have%20removed%20the%20convention%20work-power%20hierarchy%20from%20our%20organisation.%20We%20are%20more%20like%20a%20family%2C%20working%20for%20this%20village.%20And%20I%20offer%20my%20family%20members%20here%20the%20same%20courtesy%20and%20respect%20as%20they%20offer%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20getting%20curious%20about%20the%20blue%20corn%2C%20but%20CC%20goes%20marching%20onto%20the%20deep%20brown%20soil%20field%2C%20and%20calls%20me%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20young%20corn%20plants.%20The%20entire%20field%20is%20sown%20with%20blue%20corn.%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20the%20arroyo%20has%20overflowed%2C%20flooding%20some%20part%20of%20our%20fields%2C%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20plant%20corn%20there.%20But%20we%20did%20use%20the%20fields%20this%20time%20for%20hay%2C%20beans%20and%20chilly.%20As%20we%20are%20in%20the%20International%20Year%20of%20Millets%2C%20I%20even%20am%20trying%20to%20grow%20some%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eragi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eamaranth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Emillets%2C%E2%80%9D%20CC%20tells%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20already%20beyond%20lunch%20time%2C%20she%20invites%20us%20to%20the%20Sala%2C%20a%20local%20village%20cafe%20run%20by%20the%20organisation.%20Here%20Linda%20greets%20us.%20She%20explained%20%E2%80%98donation%20only%E2%80%99%20model%2C%20for%20where%20you%20only%20give%20what%20you%20can%20give%20for%20the%20food.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20way%20we%20ensure%20that%20no%20one%20in%20our%20community%20goes%20hungry.%20All%20kinds%20of%20people%20come%20here%2C%20from%20addicts%20to%20cattle%20ranchers%20and%20an%20occasion%20a%20tourist%20or%20two%2C%20we%20offer%20nutritious%20and%20healthy%20food%2C%20till%20mid%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20CC%20remarks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20pick%20up%20a%20bowl%20of%20red%20chilli%20and%20sit.%20I%20am%20moved%20with%20her%20world.%20Why%20would%20she%20choose%20to%20do%20this%3F%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20it%20because%20I%20can.%20In%20my%20life%2C%20I%20am%20free%20and%20now%20want%20to%20help%20others%20around%20me.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20the%20humans%2C%20there%20are%20beings%20I%20love%20more%20than%20humans%20too.%20Beavers%2C%20butterflies%2C%20ants%20and%20even%20the%20weeds%20in%20our%20fields%2C%20all%20need%20care%20and%20love.%20And%20I%20am%20only%20doing%20a%20small%20part%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20tells%20me%20and%20then%20points%20to%20a%20beautiful%20micaceous%20clay%20pot%2C%20next%20to%20the%20photo%20of%20her%20grand%20daughter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20legendary%20micaceous%20clay%20potter%20Felipe%20Ortega%20who%20drew%20me%20to%20this%20village.%20It%E2%80%99s%20been%20a%20few%20years%20since%20he%20has%20passed%2C%20but%20somehow%20this%20place%20feels%20like%20home.%20And%20this%20is%20a%20home%20I%20created%20for%20myself%2C%20by%20myself.%20I%20find%20peace%20and%20solitude%20here%2C%20and%20hence%20I%20continue%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20almost%20evening%20now%2C%20and%20I%20am%20still%20in%20admiration%20of%20this%20woman%E2%80%99s%20journey.%20She%20was%20born%20in%20the%20American%20South%2C%20worked%20on%20boats%20in%20California%20and%20sailed%20on%20the%20high%20seas%20and%20finally%20settled%20in%20the%20desert.%20I%20left%20with%20a%20hopeful%20feeling%20because%20her%20farm%20and%20organisation%20were%20regenerative%20in%20action.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20has%20nurtured%20many%20seeds%20and%20humans%20to%20reach%20their%20fullest%20potential%2C%20hence%20to%20all%20she%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELa%20Patrona.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20this%20dog-eat-dog%20world%2C%C2%A0%20empowering%20others%20to%20be%20of%20service%20to%20the%20earth%20is%20no%20little%20task.%20CC%20does%20it%20silently%20everyday.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Shekhar%20Singh%20is%20an%20independent%20agri-policy%20analyst%20and%20writer.%20He%20was%20the%20former%20director%2C%20policy%20and%20outreach%2C%20at%20NSAI.%20He%20also%20hosts%20The%20Wire%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20talk%20show%2C%20Krishi%20ki%20baat%2FFarm%20Talks.%20He%20tweets%20%40indrassingh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695561775000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24184618%2FIMG_0276.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fla-patrona-agriculture-new-mexico-blue-corn%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20over%20three%20and%20a%20half%20decades%2C%20C.C.%20Culver%20has%20been%20the%20driving%20force%20behind%20the%20conservation%20and%20re-wilding%20of%20the%20quaint%20rural%20high%20desert%20village%20of%20La%20Madera%2C%20New%20Mexico.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fla-patrona-agriculture-new-mexico-blue-corn%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parineeti%20and%20Raghav%20are%20now%20married!%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695561720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103908608%2Cimgsize-1677889.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fparineeti-chopra-and-raghav-chadha-are-now-married%2Farticleshow%2F103908105.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103908105.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ERaghav%20Chadha%20and%20Parineeti%20Chopra%20have%20officially%20tied%20t