2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20that%20she%20was%20harassed%20and%20died%20that%20made%20the%20news%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20because%20those%20guys%20tried%20to%20snatch%20arms%20from%20the%20policemen%20nearby%20and%20tried%20to%20run%2C%20eventually%20getting%20shot%20in%20the%20legs%20by%20the%20police.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20woman%20in%20north%20India%20would%20have%20been%20stunned%20by%20the%20news.%20Angry%2C%20yes.%20Surprised%2C%20no.%20We%20have%20all%20grown%20up%20with%20several%20incidents%20like%20this%20%E2%80%93%20mostly%20being%20%E2%80%98lucky%E2%80%99%20with%20just%20falling%2C%20scratching%20our%20knees%2C%20elbows%2C%20injuries%20to%20forehead%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20badly%20you%20fell%20and%20where%20you%20knocked%20yourself.%20When%20I%20read%20the%20news%2C%20there%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20one%20incident%20that%20cropped%20up%2C%20there%20were%20way%20too%20many%20and%20the%20anger%20didn%E2%80%99t%20subside.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20well%20known%20reasons%20for%20patriarchy%20behind%20street%20harassment%20and%20violence%2C%20especially%20in%20north%20India.%20Lots%20of%20conversations%20on%20dress%20code%20for%20women%20%E2%80%93%20mostly%20why%20they%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20wear%20western%20clothes.%20Yet%2C%20I%20have%20always%20found%20a%20severe%20lack%20of%20conversation%20on%20the%20imposition%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esalwar-kameez%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20dupatta%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(Indian%20long%20shirt%2C%20loose%20trousers%20and%20stole)%20imposed%20on%20young%20girls%20and%20women%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20turn%2012%20or%2013%2C%20and%20how%20utterly%20sexualised%20it%20is.%20Patriarchy%20starts%20from%20homes%2C%20not%20the%20streets%3B%20and%20the%20role%20of%20parents%2C%20especially%20mothers%2C%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out.%20The%20way%20they%20impose%20%E2%80%98new%20clothes%E2%80%99%20on%20their%20daughters%2C%20and%20never%20have%20a%20conversation%20with%20their%20sons%20about%20respecting%20women%20or%20even%20their%20own%20sisters.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20did%20my%20basic%20schooling%20in%20Karnal%2C%20Haryana%20because%20my%20parents%20taught%20at%20a%20college%20and%20school%20there.%20Even%20though%20Karnal%20is%20a%20town%20with%20a%20huge%20migrant%20population%20%E2%80%93%201947%20and%201984%20Punjabi%20refugees%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Jat%20culture%20still%20rules.%20Punjabis%20have%20a%20similar%20cultural%20background%20so%20in%20spite%20of%20land%20and%20resources-%20related%20animosity%2C%20they%20gel%20well%20together%20culturally.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Flaws-sexual-violence-brij-bhushan-saakhi%5C%22%3ELaws%20Alone%20Cannot%20Prevent%20Sexual%20Violence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20my%20classmates%20were%20Jats%20or%20Punjabis%2C%20we%20were%20the%20outsiders.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20conform%20to%20local%20standards%20and%20my%20parents%20were%20progressive%20enough%20to%20not%20dictate%20what%20I%20wear.%20However%2C%20a%20much%20bigger%20reason%20why%20I%20absolutely%20stayed%20away%20from%20salwar%20kameez%20and%20dupatta%20(or%20suit%20as%20is%20popularly%20known%20in%20the%20Haryana-Punjab%20region)%20while%20growing%20up%20was%20because%20I%20saw%20how%20it%20immediately%20sexualised%20the%20bodies%20of%20my%20friends%20and%20classmates%20and%20how%20street%20harassment%20exponentially%20increased%20once%20you%20started%20wearing%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20like%20a%20clear%20signal%20to%20the%20world%20that%20this%20girl%20has%20grown%20up%20and%20is%20now%20available%20for%20harassment.%20The%20dirty%20gaze%20of%20middle-aged%20and%20older%20men%20at%20school%20going%20girls%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20something%20I%20missed.%20Yet%2C%20they%20would%20return%20home%20to%20cover%20their%20daughters%20%E2%80%93%20or%20because%20of%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20growing-up%20body%20was%20a%20dirty%20thing%20to%20be%20covered%20in%20as%20many%20layers%20as%20possible.%20Unknowingly%2C%20I%20did%20the%20same.%20I%20was%20never%20a%20tomboy%20or%20enjoyed%20wearing%20denims%20but%20I%20would%20wear%20jeans%2C%20with%20a%20t-shirt%20and%20a%20loose%20shirt%20borrowed%20from%20my%20elder%20brother%E2%80%99s%20closet%20over%20it%2C%20thinking%20this%20would%20not%20catch%20attention.%20All%20these%20layers%20in%20north%20Indian%20summers%20which%20can%20easily%20touch%2045%C2%B0Celsius%20and%20riding%20a%20bicycle%20%E2%80%93%20I%20used%20to%20be%20drenched%20in%20sweat%20but%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20ever%20think%20of%20wearing%20a%20suit%20which%20is%20made%20of%20cotton%20and%20much%20more%20airy.%20Dresses%20were%20not%20even%20on%20the%20scene%20back%20in%20the%201990s%20in%20small%20towns.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20that%20this%20self-afflicted%20torture%20helped%20anything.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24164751%2F1599px-Indian_Students_4616.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24164751%2F1599px-Indian_Students_4616.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24164751%2F1599px-Indian_Students_4616-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24164751%2F1599px-Indian_Students_4616-1024x680.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674593%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22797%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Biswarup%20Ganguly%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0%2C%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20you%20were%20on%20a%20bicycle%2C%20guys%20had%20a%20thing%20called%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eside%20marna%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20which%20is%20basically%20them%20ramming%20their%20bicycle%20or%20scooter%20into%20your%20front%20tyre%20so%20that%20you%20fell.%20I%20still%20do%20not%20understand%20why%20teenage%20boys%20think%20this%20violence%20is%20funny.%20I%20have%20fallen%20so%20many%20times%20and%20been%20harassed%20during%20school%20days%20that%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20remember%20the%20count.%20If%20not%20this%2C%20then%20there%20were%20occasions%20when%20someone%20would%20come%20too%20close%20out%20of%20the%20blue%20and%20slap%20your%20breasts.%20The%20long%20term%20anger%20and%20resentment%20it%20builds%20in%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20body%20is%20not%20even%20explored.%20I%20hated%20growing%20up.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20day%2C%20I%20was%20on%20my%20way%20to%20my%20friend%E2%80%99s%20place%20with%20her%2C%20both%20of%20us%20riding%20our%20bicycles%20when%20a%20group%20of%20teenage%20boys%2C%20heading%20the%20same%20way%20as%20us%2C%20formed%20a%20ring%20around%20us.%20One%20of%20the%20boys%20was%20about%20to%20hit%20my%20friend%2C%20and%20to%20save%20herself%2C%20she%20barged%20into%20me.%20It%20had%20rained%20very%20heavily%20just%20a%20little%20while%20before%20so%20I%20went%20skidding%20for%20quite%20a%20few%20feet.%20My%20skirt%20got%20torn%2C%20my%20knees%20and%20shin%20was%20deeply%20gashed%2C%20as%20were%20my%20elbows%20and%20hands.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20guys%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20stop%20laughing%20and%20no%20passerby%20did%20anything%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20the%20norm%20in%20Karnal.%20I%20never%20witnessed%20one%20incident%20where%20any%20elderly%20person%20intervened.%20My%20friend%E2%80%99s%20mother%20cleaned%20my%20wounds%20and%20gave%20me%20one%20of%20her%20dresses%20to%20wear%20to%20go%20back%20home.%20I%20had%20to%20get%20a%20tetanus%20injection%20and%20for%20weeks%2C%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20even%20walk%20properly%20or%20move%20my%20elbow.%20This%20was%20just%20one%20of%20the%20many%20times%20I%20was%20thrown%20off%20my%20bicycle%20and%20hurt%20myself.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fmanipur-sexual-violence-bjp-apathy-patriarchy%5C%22%3EWhy%20Does%20Our%20Government%20Need%20a%20Graphic%20Depiction%20of%20Violence%20Against%20Women%20to%20Act%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20already%20started%20working%20before%20my%20mother%20retired%20from%20the%20school%2C%20and%20one%20time%20while%20I%20was%20visiting%20home%2C%20I%20went%20to%20pick%20her%20up%20in%20my%20car%20after%20school.%20I%20had%20studied%20in%20the%20same%20school%20and%20our%20uniform%20used%20to%20be%20a%20white%20shirt%2C%20navy%20blue%20skirt%20(for%20girls)%2C%20navy%20blue%20trousers%20for%20guys%2C%20along%20with%20a%20tie%20and%20belt.%20And%20black%20shoes.%20I%20used%20to%20love%20my%20uniform%20%E2%80%93%20carefully%20and%20perfectly%20creased%20pleated%20skirt%2C%20socks%20folded%20down%20with%20black%20mary-janes.%20I%20was%20waiting%20outside%20the%20school%20gate%20in%20the%20car%20for%20my%20mother%20when%20I%20saw%20girls%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20school%20in%20white%20kurta%2C%20navy%20blue%20salwar%20and%20navy%20blue%20dupatta.%20When%20my%20mother%20came%2C%20I%20asked%20her%20if%20some%20other%20school%20visiting%20or%20if%20there%20was%20some%20event%20at%20the%20school.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20told%20me%20the%20uniform%20for%20girls%20had%20changed.%20From%20grade%20seven%20or%20eight%2C%20they%20were%20supposed%20to%20wear%20this%20now.%20No%20sex%20education%2C%20no%20education%20on%20consent%2C%20on%20respecting%20women%2C%20nothing%20on%20sexual%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20the%20solution%20was%20to%20cover%20women%E2%80%99s%20bodies%20as%20they%20thought%20appropriate.%20Reinforcing%20objectification%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20bodies%20right%20from%20school%20level%2C%20make%20it%20known%20to%20the%20world%20that%20this%20is%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20body%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20covered%20head%20to%20toe%20now%20%E2%80%93%20and%20yes%2C%20now%20available%20for%20sexual%20harassment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20was%20maybe%20eight%20or%20nine%20years%20old%2C%20I%20went%20to%20visit%20a%20family%20friend%20with%20my%20mother%20on%20a%20cycle%20rickshaw.%20We%20were%20at%20a%20major%20crossing%20almost%20right%20in%20front%20of%20the%20town%20court%2C%20the%20office%20of%20Superintendent%20of%20Police%20was%20quite%20literally%2010-15%20feet%20away%2C%20and%20there%20was%20the%20body%20of%20a%20young%20woman%20lying%20on%20the%20road.%20Nobody%20did%20anything.%20People%20were%20just%20looking%20at%20her%20and%20passing%20by.%20There%20was%20no%20policeman%20around.%20I%20was%20so%20horrified%20I%20started%20screaming%20at%20my%20mother.%20Why%20isn%E2%80%99t%20anyone%20doing%20anything%3F%20Why%20aren%E2%80%99t%20they%20taking%20her%20to%20hospital%3F%20She%20will%20die.%20My%20mother%20turned%20my%20face%20to%20the%20other%20side%20and%20said%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20already%20too%20late.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20woman%20was%20wearing%20a%20suit%20%E2%80%93%20white%20kameez%20and%20a%20worn%20out%20blue%20dupatta%20tightly%20covering%20her%20head%20and%20chest.%20That%20road%20led%20towards%20where%20poor%20Dalit%20families%20lived%20back%20then.%20Her%20lifeless%20body%20was%20still%20entangled%20in%20her%20rickety%20old%20bicycle%20she%20was%20riding%2C%20apparently%20pushed%20for%20fun%20by%20some%20guy%20causing%20her%20to%20hit%20her%20head%20on%20the%20pavement.%20What%20fun!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20days%20I%20kept%20thinking%20who%20would%20tell%20her%20family%2C%20did%20they%20know%2C%20what%20if%20she%20had%20small%20kids%20at%20home%2C%20what%20would%20happen%20to%20them%3F%20The%20image%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20stopped%20haunting%20me%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EParul%20Abrol%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695555389000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F23101923%2FIMG_2534-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwhat-does-a-dupatta-mean-for-a-young-woman%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wearing%20a%20salwar-kameez%20was%20like%20a%20clear%20signal%20to%20the%20world%20that%20this%20girl%20has%20grown%20up%20and%20is%20now%20available%20for%20harassment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwhat-does-a-dupatta-mean-for-a-young-woman%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Prickly%20Nationalism%E2%80%99%3A%20From%20a%20G20%20High%20to%20a%20Post-Canada%20Low%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24171723%2FModi-Trudeau.png%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695555332000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19230651%2FH20230910138622.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fglobal-press-views-on-india-canada-row-nijjar-allegations%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justin%20Trudeau's%20allegations%20against%20India%20have%20raised%20serious%20and%20disturbing%20questions%20about%20the%20Modi%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fglobal-press-views-on-india-canada-row-nijjar-allegations%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%2