ince%20her%20far-right%20party%20won%20historic%20elections%20a%20year%20ago.%20Meloni's%20post-fascist%20Brothers%20of%20Italy%20party%20was%20elected%20largely%20on%20a%20promise%20to%20reduce%20mass%20migration%20into%20Italy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fitalian-pm-admits-she-hoped-to-do-better-on-migration%2Farticleshow%2F103907200.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fitalian-pm-admits-she-hoped-to-do-better-on-migration%2Famp_articleshow%2F103907200.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fitalian-pm-admits-she-hoped-to-do-better-on-migration%2Famp_articleshow%2F103907200.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Justice%20for%20Ganga%20Requires%20Urgent%20Collective%20Action%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24141720%2F1600px-The_Divine_Ganga_or_Ganges_River.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20last%20Sunday%20of%20September%20is%20observed%20as%20World%20Rivers%20Day.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20a%20coincidence%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fgovernment-forms-jal-shakti-ministry-by-merging-water-resources-and-drinking-water-ministries%2Farticleshow%2F69602462.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Echose%20to%20rename%20the%20water%20resource%20ministry%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9CMinistry%20of%20Jal%20Shakti%E2%80%9D%20with%20divisions%20like%20the%20Department%20of%20Drinking%20Water%20and%20Sanitation%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Water%20Resources%2C%20River%20Development%20and%20Ganga%20Rejuvenation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20departmental%20groupings%20and%20name%20modifications%20each%20have%20their%20own%20importance%2C%20purpose%2C%20results%2C%20and%20effects.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20mission%20has%20been%20clarified%20by%20the%20new%20name%2C%20which%20also%20specifies%20that%20its%20primary%20goal%20going%20forward%20will%20be%20to%20analyse%20the%20value%20and%20power%20of%20water%20and%20will%20thus%20be%20administratively%20distinct%20from%20river%20management.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20significant%20distinction%20is%20that%20the%20government%20has%20preserved%20the%20department%E2%80%99s%20name%20as%20the%20Department%20of%20River%20Development%20rather%20than%20renaming%20it%20as%20the%20River%20Basin%20Development.%20Here%2C%20the%20obvious%20goal%20is%20to%20draw%20attention%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20development%20and%20preservation%20of%20the%20river%20herself%20is%20important%20and%20is%2C%20administratively%2C%20an%20independent%20activity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20India%2C%20where%20rivers%20are%20revered%20and%20treated%20as%20religious%20entities%2C%20such%20understanding%20cannot%20be%20subject%20to%20surprise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findias-water-governance-plan-cannot-leave-out-its-people%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Water%20Governance%20Plan%20Cannot%20Leave%20Out%20Its%20People%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20religious%20significance%20of%20rivers%20in%20India%20goes%20back%20centuries%20%E2%80%93%20Hindu%20priests%20have%20bathed%20in%20rivers%20like%20Ganga%2C%20Yamuna%20and%20Sarasvati%20and%20offered%20prayers%20along%20their%20banks.%20Given%20their%20religious%20significance%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20that%20today%20these%20rivers%20are%20losing%20their%20famed%20purity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20fact%20has%20been%20highlighted%20multiple%20times%20by%20the%20Central%20Pollution%20Board.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%20the%20board%20reported%20that%2046%25%20of%20Indian%20rivers%20are%20polluted.%20It%20has%20identified%20311%20polluted%20river%20stretches%20(PRS)%20on%20279%20different%20rivers%20in%2028%20different%20states%20and%208%20union%20territories.%20The%20board%20confirmed%20that%20Ganga%20is%20the%20most%20polluted%20river%20among%20all%20the%20others.%20In%20January%202023%2C%20dangerous%20amounts%20of%20faecal%20coliform%20were%20recorded%20by%20at%20least%2071%25%20of%20the%20Ganga%E2%80%99s%20monitoring%20stations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24142908%2FGanges-Brahmaputra-Meghna_basins.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24142908%2FGanges-Brahmaputra-Meghna_basins.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24142908%2FGanges-Brahmaputra-Meghna_basins-300x166.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24142908%2FGanges-Brahmaputra-Meghna_basins-1024x567.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674564%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22665%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMap%20outlining%20the%20states%20Ganga%20passes%20through.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20commons%2FPfly%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20United%20Nations%20concurs%2C%20listing%20Ganga%20as%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20contaminated%20rivers.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20saddest%20part%20is%20that%20this%20is%20the%20case%20even%20though%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20promised%20to%20%E2%80%9Cwork%20hard%E2%80%9D%20to%20purify%20the%20Ganga%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnmcg.nic.in%2FNamamiGanga.aspx%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Namami%20Gange%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20project%2C%20and%20even%20though%20the%20Union%20has%2C%20since%202014%2C%20taken%20on%20409%20projects%20with%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1898802%5C%22%3E%20budget%20outlay%20of%20Rs%2032%2C912.40%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20clean%20up%20the%20river%2C%20as%20the%20Jal%20Shakti%20ministry%20confirmed%20in%20February%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reports%20released%20by%20different%20institutions%20confirm%20that%20reality%20does%20not%20reflect%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpriority%20commitment%E2%80%9D%20made%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGanga%20Mata%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(mother%20Ganga).%20Open%20drains%20allow%20untreated%20sewage%20and%20other%20sorts%20of%20garbage%20to%20flow%20into%20the%20Ganga%2C%20turning%20the%20river%20crimson%20in%20some%20places%20and%20producing%20clouds%20of%20deadly%20foam%20floating%20on%20the%20river%E2%80%99s%20surface%20in%20others.%20This%20happens%20in%20spite%20of%20all%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20and%20pledges.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECorruption%2C%20excessive%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20the%20union%20government%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20utilise%20the%20entire%20sum%20allocated%20for%20development%20initiatives%20are%20frequently%20cited%20as%20the%20key%20causes%20of%20the%20project%E2%80%99s%20ineffective%20performance.%20The%20argument%20is%20well-known%2C%20but%20curiously%2C%20the%20two%20most%20recent%20cases%20that%20the%20National%20Green%20Tribunal%20heard%20add%20to%20the%20narrative%20and%20reveal%20that%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20more%20complex%20than%20it%20appears.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Friver-rejuvenation-ganga-blueprint%5C%22%3EGanga%20Still%20Suffers%20%E2%80%93%20But%20Govt%20Thinks%20%E2%80%98Successful%E2%80%99%20Rejuvenation%20Is%20a%20Blueprint%20for%20Other%20Rivers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20case%20titled%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F80233351%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Subhas%20Datta%20vs.%20State%20of%20West%20Bengal%20%26amp%3B%20Others%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20it%20was%20revealed%20that%20the%20hotels%20and%20restaurants%20close%20to%20Howrah%20Railway%20Station%20were%20polluting%20the%20river%20Ganga%20with%20their%20liquid%20and%20solid%20waste.%20These%20constructions%20were%20allegedly%20illegal%2C%20according%20to%20the%20complaint.%20In%20another%20case%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F97486486%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EManoj%20Kumar%20Rai%20vs.%20State%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20tribunal%20named%20local%20governments%20as%20being%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Ganga%E2%80%99s%20pollution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20tribunal%20declared%20that%20the%20state%20administration%20failed%20to%20hold%20negligent%20personnel%20accountable%20for%20the%20misappropriation%20of%20public%20funds%20and%20for%20failing%20to%20avoid%20harm%20to%20the%20Ganga%20river.%20The%20tribunal%20has%20taken%20seriously%20the%20discharge%20of%20about%2020%20million%20litres%2Fday%20(MLD)%20of%20untreated%20sewage%20into%20the%20Ganga%20by%20various%20parties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20two%20cases%20demonstrate%20that%20a%20project%E2%80%99s%20failure%20is%20also%20because%20of%20the%20negligence%20of%20the%20private%20sector%20combined%20with%20the%20state%20administration%E2%80%99s%20failure.%20The%20two%20cases.%20and%20several%20more%20like%20them%2C%20show%20that%20in%20a%20federal%20structure%2C%20it%20is%20inappropriate%20to%20label%20every%20failure%20as%20that%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20identify%20individuals%2C%20groups%20and%20communities%20who%20contaminated%20the%20Ganga%20because%20Ganga%E2%80%99s%20waters%20flow%20through%20so%20many%20different%20states.%20Indeed%2C%20there%20are%20several%20parties%20responsible%20for%20the%20contamination%20of%20the%20river%2C%20and%20each%20has%20to%20be%20held%20accountable.%20However%2C%20regrettably%2C%20in%20India%2C%20politics%20is%20the%20sole%20lens%20used%20to%20observe%20and%20assess%20issues.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20it%20is%20true%20that%20industrialisation%20is%20the%20primary%20cause%20of%20pollution%2C%20it%20is%20also%20true%20that%20religious%20and%20cultural%20ideals%20have%20not%20effectively%20promoted%20the%20concept%20and%20practice%20of%20revitalising%20the%20Ganga.%20Religious%20sentiments%20appreciate%20and%20support%20the%20Ganga%20as%20a%20living%20entity%2C%20but%20in%20reality%2C%20things%20work%20the%20other%20way%20around.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24142128%2F6295950659_c93a8fe4bb_b.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24142128%2F6295950659_c93a8fe4bb_b.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24142128%2F6295950659_c93a8fe4bb_b-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674563%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EReligious%20rituals%20carried%20out%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20Ganga.%20Photo%3A%20Flickr%2FCC%20By%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20should%20be%20no%20hesitation%20in%20admitting%20that%20other%20than%20industrialisation%2C%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20for%20its%20contamination%20is%20related%20to%20its%20religious%20significance%20%E2%80%93%20immature%20and%20obscene%20ceremonies%20performed%20in%20the%20name%20of%20religion%20contribute%20to%20the%20issue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20project%E2%80%99s%20goals%20have%20not%20been%20met%20because%20the%20river%E2%80%99s%20water%20quality%20is%20constantly%20harmed%20by%20the%20immersion%20of%20idols%20and%20other%20religious%20objects%20during%20various%20festivals.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EDevotees%2C%20while%20commemorating%20Ganga%E2%80%99s%20sacredness%2C%20rarely%20follow%20the%20guidelines%20outlined%20as%20part%20of%20the%20action%20plan%20for%20reviving%20Ganga.%20It%20is%20absolutely%20necessary%20in%20this%20situation%20to%20reinterpret%20ritualistic%20practices%20in%20order%20to%20encourage%20each%20Indian%20to%20see%20beyond%20themselves%20and%20safeguard%20the%20river%20from%20contamination.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeeking%20to%20preserve%20the%20Ganga%20just%20because%20of%20her%20importance%20and%20utility%20is%20a%20widespread%20practice%2C%20however%2C%20it%20merely%20exemplifies%20human%20selfishness%20which%20compromise%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20river.%20This%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20further%20implies%20that%20Ganga%20should%20endure%20till%20it%20is%20beneficial%20to%20people.%20It%20is%20time%20that%20we%20went%20beyond%20self-serving%20motives%20and%20act%20collectively%20to%20save%20our%20rivers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDr.%20Deepti%20Acharya%20is%20working%20as%20senior%20Assistant%20Professor%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20The%20Maharaja%20Sayajirao%20University%20of%20Baroda%2C%20Vadodara%20and%20author%20of%20the%20Book%20Water%20and%20Public%20Polices%20in%20India%2C%20Routledge%2C%20New%20York%20and%20London%2C%202021.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695548833000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcd