sed%20the%20killing%20of%20more%20than%20160%20people%20in%20the%20state%2C%20and%20thousands%20of%20houses%20belonging%20to%20both%20Meitei%20and%20Kuki%20communities%20were%20set%20ablaze%2C%20resulting%20in%20over%2070%2C000%20people%20being%20displaced.%20These%20killings%20were%20carried%20out%20using%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20visit%20to%20Manipur%2C%20it%20was%20observed%20that%20people%20were%20openly%20carrying%20weapons%20throughout%20the%20state%2C%20even%20in%20front%20of%20state%20and%20central%20forces.%20Some%20individuals%20openly%20told%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20not%20everyone%20in%20the%20state%20possesses%20licensed%20weapons.%20Against%20this%20backdrop%2C%20it%20is%20to%20be%20seen%20if%20those%20carrying%20weapons%20in%20the%20state%20would%20heed%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F29150739%2FScreenshot-2023-05-29-at-3.07.06-PM.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F29150739%2FScreenshot-2023-05-29-at-3.07.06-PM.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F29150739%2FScreenshot-2023-05-29-at-3.07.06-PM-300x167.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F29150739%2FScreenshot-2023-05-29-at-3.07.06-PM-1024x568.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-655467%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22666%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIn%20Bishenpur%20villages%20on%20Saturday%2C%C2%A0The%20Wire%C2%A0met%20small%20teams%20of%20Meitei%20men%2C%20armed%20with%20double-barrel%20guns%20and%20bullets%2C%20to%20chase%20away%20Kukis.%20Photo%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20such%20a%20warning%20has%20been%20issued.%20On%20June%201%2C%20during%20his%20visit%2C%20Union%20home%20minister%2C%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20had%20also%20called%20for%20the%20surrender%20of%20illegal%20weapons.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20those%20who%20have%20weapons%2C%20I%20appeal%20to%20them%20to%20surrender%20the%20weapons%20before%20the%20police.%20Starting%20tomorrow%2C%20the%20police%20will%20start%20combing%20operations%20to%20find%20the%20weapons.%20If%20the%20police%20find%20the%20weapons%20from%20them%20during%20the%20combing%20operation%2C%20they%20will%20be%20dealt%20with%20strictly%20under%20stringent%20sections%20of%20the%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shah%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20thousands%20of%20weapons%20have%20been%20stolen%20by%20locals%20in%20Manipur%2C%20as%20detailed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%20%3C%2Fem%3EOn%20May%203%2C%20when%20the%20violence%20began%20in%20Manipur%2C%20500%20guns%20and%20hundreds%20of%20ammunition%20had%20been%20looted%20by%20Kuki%20miscreants%20from%20N.%20Ibomcha%E2%80%99s%20gun%20house.%20Ibomcha%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20gun%20house%2C%20had%20lodged%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20Imphal%20Police%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20May%208%2C%20Biren%20Singh%2C%20in%20his%20first%20press%20conference%20since%20the%20violence%20began%20in%20Manipur%2C%20had%20said%20that%20miscreants%20had%20snatched%201%2C041%20weapons%20and%207%2C460%20ammunition%20from%20security%20forces%20during%20the%20riot%20since%20May%203%2C%20and%20over%20800%20of%20those%20still%20remain%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2027%2C%202023%2C%20a%20few%20Meitei%20defending%20their%20village%20confirmed%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20camera%20that%20some%20of%20them%20have%20unlicensed%20guns.%20The%20story%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D9No2LcUGLwA%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20YouTube%20channel%20on%20June%2013.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fwatch-weapons-in-the-shadows-a-glimpse-into-violence-in-manipur%5C%22%3EWatch%20%7C%20Weapons%20in%20the%20Shadows%3A%20A%20Glimpse%20Into%20Violence%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2029%2C%20a%20similar%20appeal%2C%20like%20the%20latest%20one%20by%20Singh%2C%20was%20made%20to%20the%20citizens%20to%20return%20arms%20and%20ammunition%20looted%20from%20armed%20police%20battalions%20and%20police%20stations%20at%20the%20earliest%2C%20or%20legal%20action%20would%20be%20taken%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLegal%20action%20as%20per%20the%20Arms%20Act%201959%20and%20Rules%20will%20be%20taken%20in%20case%20any%20person%20is%20found%20to%20be%20in%20unauthorized%20and%20illegal%20possession%20of%20arms%20and%20ammunition%20during%20combing%20operations%20by%20security%20personnel%20or%20otherwise%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20chief%20minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20announcement%20by%20chief%20minister%20Biren%20Singh%20was%20made%20when%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20was%20present%20in%20Manipur.%20During%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20presence%20in%20the%20state%2C%20nearly%203%2C000%20weapons%20were%20looted%20again%20in%20the%20state.%20Most%20weapons%20were%20looted%20from%20police%20camps%20and%20armories%20in%20the%20capital%20city%20of%20Imphal.%20As%20the%20violence%20entered%20its%20second%20month%2C%20nearly%20100%20people%20were%20killed%2C%20and%20more%20than%20300%20people%20were%20injured%20in%20this%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%20information%20reports%20(FIRs)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fmanipur-looted-weaponry-yet-to-return-to-police-armouries-cm-appeals-afresh-for-surrender%5C%22%3Eexamined%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20indicate%20the%20loot%20of%20sophisticated%20weapons%20like%20AK%20and%20Insas%20rifles%2C%20bombs%2C%20among%20others.%20Miscreants%20also%20took%20away%20bulletproof%20jackets%20and%20set%20fire%20to%20police%20stations%20while%20Manipur%20chief%20minister%20Biren%20Singh%2C%20for%20one%20more%20time%2C%20appealed%20to%20the%20people%20on%20Monday%2C%20June%2019%2C%20to%20surrender%20arms%20that%20had%20been%20looted%20from%20police%20armories%20ever%20since%20the%20violence%20erupted%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20Manipur%20minister%2C%20L.%20Susindro%20Meitei%2C%20had%20installed%20a%20drop%20box%20at%20his%20residence%20in%20Khurai%2C%20Imphal%20East%2C%20inviting%20people%20to%20return%20the%20weapons%20looted%20or%20snatched%20from%20the%20police.%20An%208ft%20by%204ft%20banner%20put%20up%20in%20front%20of%20the%20drop%20box%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20four%20feet%20long%2C%20three-and-a-half%20feet%20wide%2C%20and%20five%20feet%20tall%20%E2%80%93%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CPlease%20drop%20your%20snatched%20weapons%20here%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CFeel%20free%20to%20do%20so.%E2%80%9D%20The%20DropBox%20was%20set%20up%20in%20June%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20response%20to%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20appeal%20filed%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fmanipur-gun-licenses-biren-singh-violence%5C%22%3Erevealed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%20the%20past%20seven%20years%2C%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government%20has%20issued%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20gun%20licenses%20in%20the%20Northeast.%20Data%20obtained%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20under%20RTI%20shows%20that%20there%20are%2035%2C117%20active%20gun%20licenses%20in%20Manipur%20%E2%80%93%20up%20from%2026%2C836%20in%20December%202016.%20Furthermore%2C%20in%20August%2C%20another%20loot%20took%20place%20at%20the%20second%20Indian%20Reserve%20Battalion%20at%20Narasena.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695484852000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F19203619%2FFyQ9vBxaIAAY1