s%20actively%20resisting%20British%20colonial%20rule%20and%20striving%20for%20independence%2C%20Krishnajipant%20Khasgiwale%20used%20the%20festival%20to%20demonstrate%20India%E2%80%99s%20unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201892%2C%20Pune%20resident%20Krishnajipant%20visited%20the%20Maratha-ruled%20Gwalior.%20There%2C%20he%20witnessed%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F261898%2Findias-oldest-ganeshotsav-was-set-up-by-a-freedom-fighter-in-1892%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraditional%20public%20celebration%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20brought%20it%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20his%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20Shrimant%20Bhausaheb%20Rangari%20and%20Balasaheb%20Natu%20%E2%80%94%20back%20home%20in%20Pune.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShrimant%20Bhausaheb%20Rangari%2C%20also%20a%20famous%20royal%20physician%20and%20a%20freedom%20fighter%2C%20saw%20potential%20in%20this%20festival%20to%20unite%20countrymen.%20So%20he%20installed%20the%20first%20%3Cem%3Esaarvajanik%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20public%20Ganesha%20idol%20in%20his%20home%20or%20%3Cem%3Ewada%3C%2Fem%3E%20located%20in%20an%20area%20called%20Shalukar%20Bol.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20idol%20was%20unique%20as%20it%20depicted%20the%20deity%20killing%20a%20demon.%20Made%20of%20wood%20and%20bran%2C%20the%20imagery%20was%20far%20from%20the%20usual%20calm%20and%20composed%20demeanour%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F261867%2Fhow-to-carve-clay-ganesh-idol-chathurthi-sustainable-hack-eco-friendly%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eof%20Lord%20Ganesh%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20this%20was%20symbolic%20of%20India%20as%20a%20nation%20fighting%20for%20its%20freedom%20against%20the%20colonialists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20gained%20more%20attention%20when%20freedom%20fighter%20Lokmanya%20Tilak%20praised%20his%20efforts%20in%20an%20article%20in%20the%20iconic%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3EKesari%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Over%20a%20century%20later%2C%20the%20original%20idol%20made%20of%20paper%20pulp%20is%20still%20worshipped%20at%20Bhausaheb%20Rangari%E2%80%99s%20wada.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDid%20you%20find%20the%20story%20interesting%3F%20Watch%20this%20short%20video%20to%20find%20out%20more%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%20%3Ciframe%20data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll%20data-origheight%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FAu35GJHjHWE%3Fenablejsapi%3D1%26autoplay%3D0%26cc_load_policy%3D0%26cc_lang_pref%3D%26iv_load_policy%3D3%26loop%3D0%26modestbranding%3D0%26rel%3D0%26fs%3D1%26playsinline%3D0%26autohide%3D2%26theme%3Ddark%26color%3Dred%26controls%3D1%26%5C%22%20data-no-lazy%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20player%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20data-origwidth%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695218070000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fimg.youtube.com%2Fvi%2FAu35GJHjHWE%2F0.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D330388%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20royal%20physician%20and%20freedom%20fighter%2C%20Shrimant%20Bhausaheb%20Rangari%20installed%20a%20unique%20idol%20of%20Lord%20Ganesha%20in%20India's%20first%20public%20%E2%80%98Ganeshotsav%E2%80%99%20to%20send%20the%20British%20a%20strong%20message%20of%20India's%20unity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F330388%2Forigin-story-oldest-public-ganeshotsav-freedom-fighter-pune-ganesha-chaturthi-video%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20India%20Can%20Learn%20From%20TN%20%26amp%3B%20MP%E2%80%99s%20Policies%20to%20Build%20Inclusive%20Schools%20Across%20the%20Country%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20published%20in%20collaboration%20with%20EkStep%20Foundation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%2025%20years%20of%20working%20in%20the%20field%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325086%2Fhow-does-inclusive-education-in-early-childhood-development-help-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einclusive%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20made%20Sonali%20Saini%20privy%20to%20a%20glaring%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20India%20lacks%20inclusive%20policies%20and%20frameworks.%20The%20issue%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20massive%20struggle%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20implementation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20talk%20on%20inclusion%2C%20but%20%3Cem%3Ehow%20do%20we%20make%20inclusive%20schools%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWithout%20inclusivity%20and%20subsequently%20good%20learning%20opportunities%2C%20India%20faces%20a%20grave%20problem%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20early%20childhood%20care%20and%20development.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20National%20Education%20Policy%20(NEP)%202020%20highlights%20that%20over%20five%20crore%20children%20currently%20in%20elementary%20school%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F309309%2Fcentral-square-foundation-teachers-guide-improves-learning-outcomes-nipun-bharat-mission%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20attained%20foundational%20literacy%20and%20numeracy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20current%20educational%20system%20is%20such%2C%20it%20adds%2C%20that%20once%20a%20student%20falls%20behind%20on%20this%20foundational%20learning%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20maintain%20a%20flat%20learning%20curve%20for%20years%2C%20perpetually%20unable%20to%20catch%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20last%20two%20decades%2C%20Sonali%20and%20her%20organisation%20Sol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%20have%20worked%20to%20understand%20this%20problem%20in%20depth.%20In%202003%2C%20she%20founded%20the%20non-profit%20to%20build%20inclusive%20education%20and%20livelihood%20solutions%20that%20use%20innovative%20tools%20to%20encourage%20better%20learning%20and%20life%20outcomes.%20They%20aim%20to%20make%20these%20solutions%20scalable%2C%20so%20they%20may%20be%20deployed%20through%20partnerships%20with%20stakeholders%20like%20other%20NGOs%2C%20the%20government%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20journey%20has%20been%20about%20%5Bfiguring%20out%5D%20what%20an%20inclusive%20school%20looks%20like%20in%20a%20country%20like%20India%2C%20which%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20very%20high%20resources%2C%20where%20even%20%5Bprocuring%5D%20crayons%2C%20chairs%2C%20tables%20is%20a%20big%20challenge%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sonali%20explains%20in%20conversation%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20have%20impacted%20four%20million%20children%20and%20young%20adults%20with%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sonali%20founded%20the%20non-profit%20SOL's%20Arc%20to%20build%20inclusive%20education%20and%20livelihood%20solutions.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484.jpg%201156w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330351%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESonali%20founded%20the%20non-profit%20Sol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%20to%20build%20inclusive%20education%20and%20livelihood%20solutions.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20%E2%80%98lifespan%20approach%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20been%20notable%20about%20Sol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%E2%80%99s%20work%20is%20its%20collaboration%20with%20state%20governments%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20to%20improve%20foundational%20literacy%20and%20inclusive%20education.%20These%20interventions%20serve%20as%20examples%20of%20how%20the%20reach%20and%20implementation%20of%20existing%20policies%20can%20be%20widened%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F311679%2Fthings-to-know-jaadui-pitara-play-based-learning-children-national-curriculum-framework%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpact%20lakhs%20of%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20there%20is%20Project%20Ankur%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20building%20Foundational%20Literacy%20(English)%C2%A0%20and%20Numeracy%20(Math)%20through%20an%20inclusive%20curriculum%20for%20teachers%20and%20students%20from%20Class%201%20to%20Class%203.%20This%20has%20been%20done%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Rajya%20Shiksha%20Kendra%2C%20the%20key%20department%20working%20towards%20the%20state%20FLN%20programme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%20analyses%20that%20non-inclusive%20pedagogy%2C%20non-conceptual%20FLN%20frameworks%2C%20and%20low%20teacher%20capacities%20are%20some%20of%20the%20key%20reasons%20why%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20vulnerable%20children%20are%20not%20learning%20as%20they%20should.%20Sonali%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20look%20at%20%5Bhigh-income%5D%20countries%2C%20their%20solutions%20were%20very%20high%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20assistive%20technology%2C%20accessible%20content%E2%80%A6that%20may%20not%20be%20possible%20in%20a%20country%20like%20ours%2C%20which%20has%20low%20digital%20penetration.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20teacher%20ratio%20and%20the%20special%20educator%20ratios%20are%20abysmal%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%20Government%20data%20suggests%20that%20the%20teacher%20ratio%20has%20fallen%20from%2043%20in%202010-11%20to%2026.3%20in%202020-%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%2C%20she%20says%2C%20focuses%20more%20on%20education%20outcomes%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20to%20subsequently%20increase%20livelihood%20opportunities.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20work%20on%20a%20lifespan%20approach%20because%20only%20working%20on%20education%20may%20not%20be%20sufficient.%20Even%20when%20we%20complete%20education%2C%20if%20the%20children%20are%20still%20sitting%20at%20home%2C%20then%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20point.%20So%20to%20improve%20life%20outcomes%2C%20we%20include%20that%20under%20our%20focus%20for%20age%20groups%20from%205-39.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201280px)%20100vw%2C%201280px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20organisation's%20UDL%20approach%20emphasises%20flexible%20learning%20environments%20that%20accommodate%20individual%20learning%20differences.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667.jpg%201280w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330354%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20organisation%E2%80%99s%20UDL%20approach%20emphasises%20flexible%20learning%20environments%20that%20accommodate%20individual%20learning%20differences.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMultiple%20children%2C%20multiple%20ways%20to%20learn%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20Project%20Ankur%2C%20the%20organisation%20has%20taken%20on%20a%20Universal%20Design%20for%20Learning%20(UDL)%20approach%20to%20teaching%20and%20learning%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cgives%20all%20students%20equal%20opportunities%20to%20succeed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUDL%20is%20a%20framework%20that%20emphasises%20flexible%20learning%20environments%20that%20accommodate%20individual%20learning%20differences.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20basically%20says%20%E2%80%98Teach%20in%20multiple%20ways%2C%20allow%20the%20child%20to%20respond%20in%20multiple%20ways%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6the%20teaching-learning%20material%20should%20have%20multiple%20modalities%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Sonali.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20aims%20to%20bring%20flexibility%20in%20these%20arenas%20so%20they%20can%20be%20adjusted%20as%20per%20an%20individual%20learner%E2%80%99s%20strengths%20and%20needs.%20They%20say%20this%20is%20a%20low-tech%2C%20low-cost%20approach%20that%20is%20suitable%20for%20low-resource%20classrooms%20in%20India.%20The%20resources%20to%20teach%20include%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20adaptable%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20to%20teach%20subtraction%2C%20a%20teacher%20may%20use%20b